		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <add>Hebrew</add> <date>Nov. 19. 1859</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have just received a letter from<lb/> my lawyer in <placeName>Charleston</placeName> summoning me home&#44; in the<lb/> most emphatic language&#44; as my personal attendance at<lb/> the settlement of some worldy affair was indispensably<lb/> necessary.  I have&#44; therefore&#44; being very busy with preparations<lb/> for my departure&#8212;only time to request you for the favor of<lb/> telling me&#44; <hi rend="underline">by return of mail</hi>&#44; <hi rend="underline">who</hi> sent you the correspond&#45;<lb/>ence between myself and the committee presenting me the<lb/> Testimonial of some of my former flock.  The cor&#45;<lb/>respondence as published&#44; but more so the accompanying<lb/> remarks make it appear&#44; as tho&#39; the presentation was<lb/> made <hi rend="underline">after</hi> I had refused the request to remain.  Just<lb/> the reverse took place.  The Ladies presented their gift on<lb/> the <date>18 of October</date>&#44; the gentleman on the <date>21</date>&#44; in the morning&#44;<lb/> and my replies to them bear the same dates respectively.<lb/>  The petition&#8212;of which I <sic>sentt</sic> you a copy <sic>inclosed</sic> with<lb/> this&#8212;was presented to me on <date>Friday</date> night&#44; at the<lb/> Synagogue&#44; after divine service&#44; and answered by me on<lb/> <date>Sunday the 23d</date>&#44; <hi rend="underline">a few hours before my departure for</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline"><placeName>New&#45;York</placeName></hi>.  I don&#39;t wish that you should make any<lb/> public use of either this letter or the copy of the petition<lb/> accompanying this&#59; both are communicated to you to give<lb/> you some intimation of the reason why I am anxious</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>to know who sent you the correspondence.  Please&#44; write<lb/> at once to the care of <hi rend="underline">Prescott&#45;House</hi>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With <persName>Mrs. M&#39;s</persName> &#38; my best regard&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">I remain&#44; in the greatest<lb/> haste</p> 
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M Mayer</persName></p>
				<p>The Sabbath&#45;Sunday movement of this city<lb/> is <hi rend="underline">exploded</hi>&#33;  The society has <hi rend="underline">dissolved</hi>&#33;  It<lb/> was a still&#45;born child.</p>
		</body>
